description:
&lt;p&gt;This post offers an excellent opportunity for an experienced paediatric nurse. We are looking for a keen and enthusiastic nurse to join our dedicated 4 bedded Paediatric HDU which cares for children from 0-16years requiring level 2 critical care. We offer a variety of experience and look after a range of specialities including paediatric surgery and general medicine, ENT, maxillofacial surgery, orthopaedics, endocrinology, respiratory, gastroenterology, and are well developed in our non-invasive ventilatory support. Our philosophy is to work closely together with the multidisciplinary team in a friendly environment with a commitment to the provision of high quality paediatric critical care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A minimum of 18 months experience at Band 5 and a teaching / mentorship qualification are essential. Ideally the successful applicant will have a PILs or EPLS qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should be confident in your nursing abilities, well organised, forward thinking, proactive, have excellent communication skills and be a team player. If you are keen to work closely with critically ill children and their families to provide high quality care we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
